 211→// protectedDirs returns the list of directories to protect. This combines
 212→// static infrastructure dirs with agent-reported dirs from the registry.
 213→// The result is cached via sync.Once since it's called per-file during filepath.Walk.
 214→//
 215→// NOTE: The cache is never invalidated. In production this is fine (the agent registry
 216→// is populated at init time and never changes). However, tests that mutate the agent
 217→// registry after the first call to protectedDirs/isProtectedPath will see stale results.
 218→// If you need to test isProtectedPath with a custom registry, either:
 219→//   - run those tests in a separate process, or
 220→//   - call resetProtectedDirsForTest() to clear the cache.
 221→func protectedDirs() []string {
 222→	protectedDirsOnce.Do(func() {
 223→		protectedDirsCache = append([]string{gitDir, entireDir}, agent.AllProtectedDirs()...)
 224→	})
 225→	return protectedDirsCache
 226→}
